  "bio": [
    "Barry Bentley and his brother Keith founded infrastructure engineering software provider Bentley Systems in 1984.",
    "The company, which went public in 2020, develops and sells computer-aided design (CAD) software for architects and engineers working on public and industrial infrastructure.",
    "A third brother, Greg, served as CEO for more than two decades before transitioning into the role of executive chair and president in 2024.",
    "A fourth brother, Raymond, serves as a director.",
    "The $1.5 billion (2025 sales) company remains majority owned by the Bentley family."
  ],
